29/* umul_hi(h, x, y) puts in h the high part of x*y */
30#ifdef HAVE_MULX_U64
31#include <immintrin.h>
32#define umul_hi(h, x, y) _mulx_u64 (x, y, (unsigned long long *) &h)
33#else
34#define umul_hi(h, x, y) \
35 do { \
36 mp_limb_t _l; \
37 umul_ppmm (h, _l, x, y); \
38 } while (0)
39#endif

108/* Implements Algorithm 2 from "Improved Division by Invariant Integers",
109 Niels Möller and Torbjörn Granlund, IEEE Transactions on Computers,
110 volume 60, number 2, pages 165-175, 2011. */
111#define __gmpfr_invert_limb(r, d) \
112 do { \
113 mp_limb_t _d, _d0, _i, _d40, _d63, _v0, _v1, _v2, _e, _v3, _h, _l; \
114 _d = (d); \
115 _i = (_d >> 55) - 256; /* i = d9 - 256 */ \
116 _v0 = invert_limb_table[_i]; \
117 _d40 = (_d >> 24) + 1; \
118 _v1 = _v0 - ((invert_limb_table2[_i] * _d40) >> 40) - 1; \
119 _v2 = (_v1 << 13) + \
120 ((_v1 * ((MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 60) - _v1 * _d40)) >> 47); \
121 _d0 = _d & 1; \
122 _d63 = ((_d - 1) >> 1) + 1; \
123 _e = - _v2 * _d63 + ((_v2 & -_d0) >> 1); \
124 umul_hi (_h, _v2, _e); \
125 _v3 = (_v2 << 31) + (_h >> 1); \
126 umul_ppmm (_h, _l, _v3, d); \
127 /* v3 is too small iff (h+d)*2^64+l+d < 2^128 */ \
128 add_ssaaaa(_h, _l, _h, _l, _d, _d); \
129 MPFR_ASSERTD(_h == MPFR_LIMB_ZERO || -_h == MPFR_LIMB_ONE); \
130 (r) = _v3 - _h; \
131 } while (0)
132
133/* same algorithm, but return the value v3, which is such that
134 v3 <= invert_limb (d) <= v3 + 1 */
135#define __gmpfr_invert_limb_approx(r, d) \
136 do { \
137 mp_limb_t _d, _d0, _i, _d40, _d63, _v0, _v1, _v2, _e, _h; \
138 _d = (d); \
139 _i = (_d >> 55) - 256; /* i = d9 - 256 */ \
140 _v0 = invert_limb_table[_i]; \
141 _d40 = (_d >> 24) + 1; \
142 _v1 = _v0 - ((invert_limb_table2[_i] * _d40) >> 40) - 1; \
143 _v2 = (_v1 << 13) + \
144 ((_v1 * ((MPFR_LIMB_ONE << 60) - _v1 * _d40)) >> 47); \
145 _d0 = _d & 1; \
146 _d63 = ((_d - 1) >> 1) + 1; \
147 _e = - _v2 * _d63 + ((_v2 & -_d0) >> 1); \
148 umul_hi (_h, _v2, _e); \
149 (r) = (_v2 << 31) + (_h >> 1); \
150 } while (0)

209/* Implements Algorithm 3 from "Improved Division by Invariant Integers",
210 Niels Möller and Torbjörn Granlund, IEEE Transactions on Computers,
211 volume 60, number 2, pages 165-175, 2011. */
212#define __gmpfr_invert_limb(r, d) \
213 do { \
214 mp_limb_t _d, _d0, _d10, _d21, _d31, _v0, _v1, _v2, _e, _h, _l; \
215 _d = (d); \
216 _d0 = _d & 1; \
217 _d10 = _d >> 22; \
218 _d21 = (_d >> 11) + 1; \
219 _d31 = ((_d - 1) >> 1) + 1; \
220 _v0 = invert_limb_table[_d10 - 512]; \
221 umul_ppmm (_h, _l, _v0 * _v0, _d21); \
222 _v1 = (_v0 << 4) - _h - 1; \
223 _e = - _v1 * _d31 + ((_v1 & - _d0) >> 1); \
224 umul_ppmm (_h, _l, _v1, _e); \
225 _v2 = (_v1 << 15) + (_h >> 1); \
226 umul_ppmm (_h, _l, _v2, d); \
227 /* v2 is too small iff (h+d)*2^32+l+d < 2^64 */ \
228 add_ssaaaa(_h, _l, _h, _l, _d, _d); \
229 MPFR_ASSERTD(_h == MPFR_LIMB_ZERO || -_h == MPFR_LIMB_ONE); \
230 (r) = _v2 - _h; \
231 } while (0)
232
